


# Major things
- floating-point support
- libbcc
- retire the preliminary bcl wrapper


# Linking support
- support for shared libraries
- fix ordering of object files & libraries


# libbcc
- crtbegin.o, crtend.o
- libbcc.a
- move some compiler builtins to libbcc


# Language
- proper switch/case
- labels & goto
- add configure option to disable extensions
- add support for strings containing '\0' values
- allow support for old C-style (function) pointers


# IR-generation
- more advanced optimization techniques


# Architecture-specific related
General:
- passing/returning structs/unions

x86:
- fix nasm warning for indirect function calls (64bit)
- optimize function calls

riscv:
- more simple optimizations
- add VLAs


# Pre-processor
- more test cases for macro expansion
- support for variadic macros


# Test suite
- simplify
- fix bugs
- remove _GNU_SOURCE dependency
- make test2 be usable without installation of libbcc


# Other
- find & fix reason for random crashes
- options: -g, --sysroot=
- <stdarg.h> header
- auto-detection of --with-cpu= & --with-abi=

